**\# 🧠 Brain Tumor Detection Web App**

A web-based application for detecting brain tumors in MRI scans using an ensemble of two deep learning models: a custom CNN and a fine-tuned MobileNet. The app also provides Grad-CAM visualizations to highlight regions of interest in the scan.

![][image1]  
![][image2]  
\---

\#\# 🚀 Features

\- 📤 Upload brain MRI scans (\`.jpg\`, \`.jpeg\`, \`.png\`)  
\- 🔍 Detect presence of brain tumor using \*\*ensemble of two models\*\*  
\- 🎯 Shows model-wise confidence scores  
\- 🖼️ Generates \*\*Grad-CAM heatmap\*\* highlighting tumor regions  
\- ⚙️ Adjustable ensemble weights and prediction threshold  
\- 🧪 MRI image validation check based on color-channel consistency

\---

\#\# 🧠 Models Used

| Model        | Input Size | Description                        |  
|--------------|------------|------------------------------------|  
| \`best\_cnn.keras\` | 400x400     | Custom CNN trained on brain MRI data |  
| \`best\_mobilenet.keras\` | 224x224     | Transfer learning using MobileNet      |

Both models are trained for \*\*binary classification\*\*: \`Tumor\` vs \`No Tumor\`.

\#\# ⚙️ Setup Instructions

\#\#\# 🐍 1\. Create Virtual Environment

python \-m venv venv  
source venv/bin/activate   \# On Windows: venv\\Scripts\\activate  
📦 2\. Install Dependencies

pip install \-r requirements.txt

Requirements.txt file:-

Flask  
tensorflow  
Pillow  
numpy

🔧 3\. Place Models  
Put the trained .keras models in the models/ folder:

models/best\_cnn.keras

models/best\_mobilenet.keras

💡 Usage  
🖥️ Run Flask App

python [app.py](http://app.py)

The app will be available at:  
📍 http://127.0.0.1:5000/

📤 Upload & Predict  
Visit the web page

Upload an MRI image

Optionally set:

w1, w2: weights for ensemble

threshold: decision threshold

heatmap: true/false to generate Grad-CAM

View results with confidence scores and heatmap overlay

📊 Example API Request (cURL)  
bash  
Copy  
Edit  
curl \-X POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/predict \\  
  \-F "file=@sample\_mri.jpg" \\  
  \-F "w1=0.6" \\  
  \-F "w2=0.4" \\  
  \-F "threshold=0.5" \\  
  \-F "heatmap=true"  
🖼️ Output JSON  
json  
Copy  
Edit  
{  
  "report": {  
    "model1\_confidence": 89.23,  
    "model2\_confidence": 91.01,  
    "ensemble\_confidence": 90.12,  
    "prediction": "Brain Tumor Detected"  
  },  
  "image\_url": "/static/uploads/1717445594\_scan.jpg",  
  "heatmap\_url": "/static/heatmaps/heat\_1717445595.png"  
}
